task.summary: Created Simulation Functions file and ran simulation to determine market history. I have unduely high variation (i.e. it appears as though the market behavior is incredibly erratic, even for different alpha ranges. (the resultant graphs are in clear disagreement with the top of pg 6 of Morro's Summary work.

I've established a test build to find out what leads to the indeterminancy in my procedurally generated strategies. We want a new-ish strategy for every call with a unique parameter, but the same strategy for every given parameter. I'm playing with the staticness of elements of the functions, but I'll likely need to establish some catch protocols to test what exactly is happening.
